If anthros were to exist, it’s unlikely that the world will be divided by species in any significant way, beyond biologically, I guess. I mean, there would probably be isolated groups, but when it comes to the wider scale, it’s more likely that groups that live near each other would choose to live together to maximize their chance of survival. As such, many ethnic groups would likely be tied down less by species and more by cultural identity and spoken language.
I mention this because I see a lot of people lump “anthros” as a separate group from humans as a whole, and real world geopolitics is not even close to that simple. Also, species might play a role in personal identity, but this post is more about the wider scale.
